column1: ##how to compute calibration equivalent to coax case
## a,b : coord on laser plane / chessboard [mm]
## dp: pixel size (as in wm config)
## t: angle between laser plane and optical axis
## such that x= a, y = b * sin(t), z = b * cos(t)
## Chessboard with square size = GridDelta [mm], resulting in calibration equivalent to coax
## pixel increment horizontal = GridDelta * beta0 / dp
## pixel increment vertical = pixel increment horizontal * sin(t)
#equivalent to coax beta0=0.4717 betaz=0.501019963968 triang angle = 46.7265007059  square size [pix] = 445,324
##equivalent to coax beta0=0.4717 betaz=0.501019963968 triang angle = 46.7265007059  square size [pix] = 445,324 + deviation
